init_text: All of the "#1 Dad" mugs in the world change to show the actual ranking of Dads suddenly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: One of the best gifts a Dads can receive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So most people just kept them in their kitchens.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It was all the talk among the kids, but it didn’t matter.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The adults also found out that the mugs had to be paired up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: That was a conversation no one wanted to have.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A group called "The Mugs of Equality" started producing and distributing a new kind of mug.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: Every household - no matter if there were parents or how many parents there were - received one #1 Family mug. And the government chipped in on the effort too - for every #1 Dad mug turned in to the local IRS office

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The group distributed them at churches, schools and community events.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: , but since there were no more #1 Dad mugs, it wasn't as big of an issue.
